\pard\f0\fs28   {\b 4. L. pseudolaxiflora} Lojac.,{\i  Fl. Sic.}{\b  2}({\b 2}): 132 (1907). Like {\b 3} but stems decumbent; leaves not more than 10 × 4 mm; pedicels c. 6 mm, much longer than bracts; corolla 15-17 mm, mainly blue; spur 7-8 mm; seeds strongly ruminate.{\i  Gozo, Linosa, Lampedusa, Malta.} Si.
