\pard\f0\fs28  {\b  L. laxiflora} Desf.,{\i  Fl. Atl.}{\b  2}: 45 (1798), from N.W. Africa, differs in having the corolla 18-23 mm, usually deep violet, the spur 10-14 mm, the lobes of the upper lip somewhat divergent, and pale brown seeds; it has been doubtfully recorded from Sicilia.
