\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 11. L. bipunctata} (L.) Dum.-Courset,{\i  Bot. Cult.}{\b  2}: 93 (1802) ({\i L. filifolia} Lag.). Annual, glandular-puberulent at least above; stems 15-30 cm, diffuse or ascending to erect, usually much-branched. Leaves 6-20 × 0·5-1 mm, linear, obtuse, verticillate below, alternate above. Racemes short, rather dense at anthesis, lax in fruit; pedicels 1-3 mm. Calyx 2·5-3 mm; lobes oblong, subobtuse, unequal. Corolla 11-14 mm, yellow; spur 4-6 mm, often reddish. Capsule c. 3·5 mm. Seeds c. 0·6 mm, flattened-trigonous to reniform, obscurely and sparsely rugose or minutely tuberculate, with rounded angles.{\i  Cultivated ground, waste places and maritime sands. • Portugal, W. & C. Spain.} Hs Lu.
